&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;United Aircraft Corporation.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hindustan Aeronautics Limited (HAL) has signed an MoU with Russia&amp;rsquo;s United Aircraft Corporation (UAC) for the production of SJ-100 civil commuter aircraft in India, marking a major milestone for indigenous civil aviation manufacturing.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The SJ-100 is expected to revolutionize short-haul connectivity under the Government&amp;rsquo;s UDAN Scheme.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This will be the first complete passenger aircraft to be manufactured in India, aligning with the &amp;lsquo;Aatmanirbhar Bharat&amp;rsquo; vision.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The collaboration is a significant step in building domestic capability in aircraft design and production.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Defence Minister Rajnath Singh termed the MoU a game changer for India&amp;rsquo;s civil aviation sector.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Hindustan Aeronautics Limited (HAL)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Established: 1940&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Headquarters: Bengaluru, Karnataka&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A leading aerospace and defence PSU engaged in the design, development, and manufacture of aircraft and helicopters.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;United Aircraft Corporation (UAC)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Founded: 2006&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Headquarters: Moscow, Russia&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Parent Organisation: Rostec State Corporation&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Specializes in the development and manufacturing of civil and military aircraft including the Sukhoi Superjet (SJ-100).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;UDAN Scheme&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Full Form: Ude Desh ka Aam Naagrik&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Launched: 2016&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Aims to enhance regional air connectivity and make air travel affordable to common citizens.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Impact&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The SJ-100 project will boost local manufacturing, create job opportunities, and strengthen private participation in aviation.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It represents a major step toward self-reliance in civil aircraft production.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ethiopia.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ethiopia is set to be confirmed as the host of the COP32 Climate Summit in 2027, following an agreement in principle during COP30 held in Belem, Brazil.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The 2027 COP32 summit will be held in Addis Ababa, the capital of Ethiopia.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Ethiopia&amp;rsquo;s bid was launched in September 2025 and later unanimously endorsed by the Bureau of African Countries, defeating Nigeria&amp;rsquo;s competing proposal.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The final formal adoption of Ethiopia as host is expected shortly during COP30 proceedings.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;COP summits rotate among regional groups; COP32 falls under the African region&amp;rsquo;s turn.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;COP30 (2025) is hosted by Brazil in Belem, while COP31 (2026) host is undecided &amp;mdash; with Australia and Turkey both in contention.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;COP (Conference of the Parties):&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Annual UN conference where nations negotiate global climate policies under the UNFCCC (United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change).&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Previous editions include COP28 (UAE, 2023) and COP29 (Azerbaijan, 2024).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Host Rotation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Regional rotation ensures global representation &amp;mdash; Africa, Asia-Pacific, Latin America, Western Europe, and Eastern Europe take turns hosting.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Andr&amp;eacute; Corr&amp;ecirc;a do Lago:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; President of COP30 (Brazil) who confirmed Ethiopia&amp;rsquo;s selection and urged Western countries to finalize the COP31 host.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Potential COP31 Hosts:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; Australia (in partnership with Pacific Islands) and Turkey remain the main contenders; if unresolved, Bonn (Germany) may host by default.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

