&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;India and Mongolia signed &lt;strong&gt;10 MoUs&lt;/strong&gt; following bilateral talks between Prime Minister Narendra Modi and Mongolian President Khurelsukh Ukhnaa in New Delhi.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The MoUs cover areas such as &lt;strong&gt;humanitarian aid, heritage restoration, immigration, geology, mineral resources, cooperatives, and digital solutions.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;On this occasion, both leaders released commemorative stamps marking the &lt;strong&gt;70th anniversary of India-Mongolia bilateral relations&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;India will provide &lt;strong&gt;free e-visas&lt;/strong&gt; to Mongolian citizens and sponsor the annual visit of young cultural ambassadors from Mongolia.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The MoUs include significant agreements on the &lt;strong&gt;oil refinery project&lt;/strong&gt; and digital cooperation between the two nations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Partnership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;: The joint statement aims to strengthen the strategic partnership between India and Mongolia, focusing on global issues and bilateral cooperation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Oil Refinery Project&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;: Built with India&amp;rsquo;s &lt;strong&gt;1.7 billion US dollars line of credit&lt;/strong&gt;, this project will boost Mongolia&amp;rsquo;s energy security.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Digital Cooperation MoU&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;: A key agreement focused on enhancing collaboration in the field of digital technologies between the two countries.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mongolian Air Carrier&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;: A Mongolian airline is preparing to operate charter flights to &lt;strong&gt;Amritsar and New Delhi&lt;/strong&gt;, strengthening bilateral tourism and business links.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GSLV-F15&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ISRO&lt;/strong&gt; achieved its historic &lt;strong&gt;100th launch&lt;/strong&gt; from the &lt;strong&gt;Satish Dhawan Space Centre (SDSC), Sriharikota&lt;/strong&gt; in &lt;strong&gt;January 2025&lt;/strong&gt; using the launch vehicle &lt;strong&gt;GSLV-F15&lt;/strong&gt;, carrying the navigation satellite &lt;strong&gt;NVS-02&lt;/strong&gt; to a &lt;strong&gt;Geosynchronous Transfer Orbit (GTO)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GSLV-F15&lt;/strong&gt; is a mission of the &lt;strong&gt;Geosynchronous Satellite Launch Vehicle (GSLV) Mk II&lt;/strong&gt; family, a &lt;strong&gt;three-stage&lt;/strong&gt; rocket with a large &lt;strong&gt;solid first stage&lt;/strong&gt;, four &lt;strong&gt;liquid strap-on boosters&lt;/strong&gt;, a &lt;strong&gt;liquid second stage&lt;/strong&gt;, and an &lt;strong&gt;indigenous cryogenic upper stage&lt;/strong&gt;, enabling the launch of &lt;strong&gt;~2&amp;ndash;2.3 tonne class&lt;/strong&gt; satellites to &lt;strong&gt;GTO&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This mission was the &lt;strong&gt;17th flight&lt;/strong&gt; of the &lt;strong&gt;GSLV series&lt;/strong&gt; and the &lt;strong&gt;11th flight&lt;/strong&gt; using an &lt;strong&gt;indigenous cryogenic engine&lt;/strong&gt;, showcasing India&amp;rsquo;s progress in complex &lt;strong&gt;cryogenic propulsion technology&lt;/strong&gt;, which is crucial for placing heavier payloads into high-energy orbits.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NVS-02&lt;/strong&gt;, the payload on &lt;strong&gt;GSLV-F15&lt;/strong&gt;, is the &lt;strong&gt;second-generation navigation satellite&lt;/strong&gt; in India&amp;rsquo;s &lt;strong&gt;NavIC (Navigation with Indian Constellation)&lt;/strong&gt; system, designed to enhance &lt;strong&gt;positioning, navigation and timing (PNT)&lt;/strong&gt; services over &lt;strong&gt;India&lt;/strong&gt; and adjoining regions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The launch from the &lt;strong&gt;Second Launch Pad&lt;/strong&gt; at &lt;strong&gt;SDSC-SHAR&lt;/strong&gt; marked an important milestone in ISRO&amp;rsquo;s operational history, symbolising more than four decades of launch operations starting from the &lt;strong&gt;SLV-3&lt;/strong&gt; era to advanced &lt;strong&gt;GSLV&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;LVM3&lt;/strong&gt; missions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;GSLV-F15&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About GSLV-F15 and GSLV family:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GSLV&lt;/strong&gt; (Geosynchronous Satellite Launch Vehicle) is India&amp;rsquo;s medium-lift launcher, primarily used to place &lt;strong&gt;communication&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;navigation satellites&lt;/strong&gt; into &lt;strong&gt;GTO&lt;/strong&gt;, typically in the &lt;strong&gt;2&amp;ndash;2.5 tonne&lt;/strong&gt; mass range.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;cryogenic upper stage&lt;/strong&gt; of GSLV uses &lt;strong&gt;liquid oxygen (LOX)&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;liquid hydrogen (LH₂)&lt;/strong&gt;, offering higher &lt;strong&gt;specific impulse&lt;/strong&gt; and making it suitable for high-energy orbits compared to purely chemical storable propellants.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GSLV-F15&lt;/strong&gt; specifically carried &lt;strong&gt;NVS-02&lt;/strong&gt; with a lift-off mass of around &lt;strong&gt;2,250 kg&lt;/strong&gt;, reinforcing India&amp;rsquo;s capability to deploy advanced navigation payloads independently.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

